**Setup for a new Adafruit Feather M0 with WiFi (WINC1500)**

This step is a one-time procedure for new, out of bag, FeatherM0 WiFi boards (Adafruit). 

**NOTE: This procedure only works with the old Arduino IDE that has the round icon![][image1](V1.x)**   
**It does not work on the new IDE with the square icon ![][image2](V2.x)** 

1- Open the old Arduino IDE (V1.x) If you donâ€™t have it installed, download and set it up. You can have both versions on your computer.

2- Check that the latest WiFi101 library is installed. If not, install or update it.

3- Open the following arduino sketch: **Examples \> WiFi101 \> FirmwareUpdater**

4- In the example, add the line of code shown below at lines 43:

![][image3]

This instruction sets the control pins in the program to work with the Feather M0 Wifi board

5- Upload the code. Do not open the Serial Monitor.

6- At the top of the Arduino IDE window, go to **Tools \> WiFi101 / WiFiNINA Firmware Updater** as shown here:

![][image4]

You will get the following window:

![][image5]

7- Test the connection between your computer and the FeatherM0WiFi with **1\. Select port of the WiFi module.**

8- **2\. Update Firmware.** Select the latest version of the WINC1501 Model B (19.6.1 in the picture above).

9- **3\. Update SSL root certificates.** Select **Add domain.** Enter [**www.google.com**](http://www.google.com) . Repeat and enter **script.google.com** so that your window is like this:

![][image6]

10- Select **Upload Certificates to WiFi module** and the Feather M0 WiFi board is ready for use with Google.

**More info at (** [Updating Firmware](https://learn.adafruit.com/adafruit-feather-m0-wifi-atwinc1500/updating-firmware) )
